reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I wish I could give Six stars; these things are excellent!
reviews.reviewText: Every one of the four GPS modules I bought grabbed a 5-satellite lock in just a few seconds - from my basement.These things are seriously nice, high-performers that I can't believe cost so little.I have not tested all of their features, but so far they just "worked" when connected to devices that use GPS modules.As soon as I need more, I'll be looking for these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Customer Support Resolved my Issue
reviews.reviewText: One of the modules arrived DOA and I didn't realize it until 60 days after purchase. Even though the return window may have already closed, the seller made things right. As for the product’s capability, if the device gets a clear view to the sky it is fairly accurate with most of its readings within a few yards. Once in a while you might get an outlier but if you normalize the data it’s easily worked around. I’m using the device with an ESP32 Microcontroller and am happy with its reliability and performance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works, easy to configure
reviews.reviewText: I got everything working with no problem. I used a USB to UART/Serial cable and connected the Pins, and it workedI was curious if this has a Compass of any type ? I suspect it does not, and only show GPS positioning.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works, no issues, nothing not to like
reviews.reviewText: Two U-Blox 7 modules with antennas for 18 bucks, work as expected out of the box, no issues, nothing not to like.If you have a Linux box, you can get on the air with these babies in about 2 minutes: The first 1:55 with an eye loupe to connect the antenna, the last 5 seconds to plug it into a USB port. Reports USB device info as follows: idVendor = 0x1546 (U-Blox) idProduct = 0x01a7 (U-blox 7)which is then claimed by low-level ACM driver cdc_acm and shows up as /dev/ttyACMn, 9600 bps, 8N1. And at that point it's "just another GPS", and you can have fun with whatever userland utilities you like to configure and/or just gobble GNSS sentences (binary or NMEA, take your pick, U-Blox 7 supports both options.)Observed self-ID sentences immediately after power-up: $GPTXT,01,01,02,ANTSTATUS=OK*3B $GPTXT,01,01,02,u-blox ag - www.u-blox.com*50 $GPTXT,01,01,02,HW UBX-G70xx 00070000 FF7FFFFFo*69 $GPTXT,01,01,02,ROM CORE 1.00 (59842) Jun 27 2012 17:43:52*59 $GPTXT,01,01,02,PROTVER 14.00*1E $GPTXT,01,01,02,ANTSUPERV=AC SD PDoS SR*20The very bottom line on the label of the units I received is 2311, probably a date code (i.e. November 2023) but not sure that's right. Not confirmed.Both the units I received obtained cold-start 2D fix in about 2 minutes, 3D fix about a minute later, indoors, above grade, with the supplied ceramic antennas. In steady-state, usually sees between 15-25 sats, uses 6 or 7.CEP is surprisingly large even with 6-7 sats, usually around 25m. Can't explain that. The actual reported location is within about 3m most of the time.For $9 each, what's not to like? Five stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Work just fine, but you need soldering skills
reviews.reviewText: These units work as expected when outside with a clear view of the sky. They also power an active GPS antenna and work even better. You do need to solder on the connector pins.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is a re-order - mighty good performance
reviews.reviewText: This is a re-order from the same source and same GPS receiver. I was really impressed with my first purchase of this "cheap" Chinese GPS neo-6 knockoff. So months later I bought two more for another project and as a backup. I attached both GPS units to a power source to see if I'd get lucky and within 2 minutes they both had acquired a 3D fix on my location from a "cold start". Mighty good performance. I use these GPS units to supply time, frequency and location information for amateur radio WSPR transmission.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple and accurate product
reviews.reviewText: I got this in my hand today and within 30 minutes I was able to connect it to Raspberry Pi 4 via USB and get the GPS reading in python code without any issues. I would highly recommend this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great value. Dont forget to change the GPS serial baud to 9600 in your code, most of the libraries default to 4800. search GitHub for TinyGPSPlus by mikalhart, decent library.
